Rating: 4
Really outstanding. Used Yukon Gold potatoes because that's what I had and they looked absolutely fabulous and tasted wonderful! Don't hesitate to make these for company - they're beautiful. I was worried that the butter would burn (450 degrees for 45 min), but didn't - just a great caramelized color on the cut side of the potatoes.

Rating: 4
I have made this four times already this summer! Rated SO highly because its [a] simply elegant [b] has the "wow" factor of a never-before-seen dish for guests and [c] very versatile: I have ventured far afield from using mere parsely. The 3-D herbs don't work [like a sprig of rosemary or basil] because they don't stick. BUT you can use rosemary if you pull the individual leaves off the stem - can arrange in a "starburst" design, etc. Other winners: sage, lemon verbena, summer savory, fennel or dill - mix & match for delightful result.

